==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clairvoyant
<hw>Clair*voy"ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>clair</ets> clear + <ets>voyant</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>voir</ets> to
see. See <er>Clear</er>, and <er>Vision</er>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to
clairvoyance; discerning objects while in a mesmeric state which are not
present to the senses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clairvoyant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Clairvoyant
<hw>Clair*voy"ant</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who is able, when in a
mesmeric state, to discern objects not present to the senses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

